Chaos erupted on Point Road, Durban when students embarked in protest action, blocking the road with stones and burning tyres on Monday morning. It is alleged that the students took to the streets over Wifi connection issues. According to Lieutenant Colonel Nqobile Gwala, Public Order Police and local police are monitoring the situation. “Two suspects aged 20 and 25 were arrested for public violence. They will appear before the Durban Magistrates’ Court tomorrow,” said Gwala.